# Enhanced IoT System for Rural Reservoir Water Level Monitoring
## Addressing Cost, Energy, Reliability, Error Handling & Maintainability

---

## System Architecture Overview

```
[Reservoir Site] → [Local Gateway] → [Cloud/Local Server] → [End Users]
     ↓                    ↓                  ↓                    ↓
  Redundant Sensors   Store & Forward   Offline Capable    Multi-channel
  Hybrid Power        Error Detection   Local Processing   Alerts
  Diagnostics         Fallback Comms    Data Sovereignty   Simple UI
```

---

## 1. COST-OPTIMIZED SENSOR LAYER

### Tiered Sensor Strategy (Addresses Cost & Reliability)

**Primary: Ultrasonic Sensor (Budget Option)**
- **Model**: JSN-SR04T-2.0 waterproof variant (~$8-12)
- **Justification**: 80% lower cost than pressure transducers
- **Mitigation for limitations**:
  - Mount at 15° angle to reduce rain interference
  - Use averaging of 10 readings (discard outliers)
  - Temperature compensation via lookup table

**Secondary: Simple Float Switch (Redundancy)**
- **Model**: Magnetic reed switch float (~$5-8)
- **Purpose**: Binary high/low threshold verification
- **Benefit**: Mechanical backup requires no power, validates ultrasonic readings

**Cost Comparison Table**:
```
Component               Budget Option    Premium Option    Savings
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Primary Sensor         $10 (Ultrasonic)  $250 (Pressure)   $240
Secondary Validation   $6 (Float)        $50 (Radar)       $44
Total Sensor Cost      $16               $300              $284
```

### Sensor Error Handling Implementation

**Multi-layer Validation**:
```cpp
struct SensorReading {
  float value;
  uint8_t confidence;  // 0-100%
  uint32_t timestamp;
  uint8_t error_flags;
};

#define ERR_TIMEOUT      0x01
#define ERR_OUT_OF_RANGE 0x02
#define ERR_VARIANCE     0x04
#define ERR_FLOAT_MISMATCH 0x08

SensorReading getValidatedReading() {
  SensorReading result;
  float readings[10];
  uint8_t valid_count = 0;

  // Take 10 readings over 5 seconds
  for(int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
    readings[i] = readUltrasonic();
    if(readings[i] > 0) valid_count++;
    delay(500);
  }

  // Insufficient valid readings
  if(valid_count < 5) {
    result.confidence = 0;
    result.error_flags |= ERR_TIMEOUT;
    return result;
  }

  // Calculate median (robust to outliers)
  result.value = calculateMedian(readings, valid_count);

  // Check variance
  float variance = calculateVariance(readings, valid_count);
  if(variance > MAX_VARIANCE) {
    result.confidence = 50;
    result.error_flags |= ERR_VARIANCE;
  } else {
    result.confidence = 90;
  }

  // Cross-validate with float switch
  bool float_high = digitalRead(FLOAT_PIN);
  bool ultrasonic_high = (result.value > THRESHOLD);

  if(float_high != ultrasonic_high) {
    result.confidence -= 30;
    result.error_flags |= ERR_FLOAT_MISMATCH;
  }

  // Range sanity check
  if(result.value < MIN_LEVEL || result.value > MAX_LEVEL) {
    result.confidence = 0;
    result.error_flags |= ERR_OUT_OF_RANGE;
  }

  result.timestamp = getTimestamp();
  return result;
}
```

---

## 2. ENERGY-OPTIMIZED EDGE DEVICE

### Hardware Selection (Cost vs. Power Trade-offs)

**Microcontroller: STM32L0 Series** (Instead of ESP32)
- **Model**: STM32L071 (~$2-3 in volume)
- **Justification**:
  - Deep sleep: 0.3μA (vs ESP32's 10μA = 33x better)
  - No WiFi/Bluetooth (unnecessary power drain)
  - Better ADC linearity than ESP32
  - Industrial temp range: -40°C to 85°C
- **Trade-off**: Requires external radio module (LoRa/cellular)

**Alternative for Easy Maintenance**: Arduino Pro Mini clone (~$2)
- Easier for local technicians to understand/replace
- Higher power consumption (sleep ~5μA) but acceptable with solar
- Widely available in developing regions

### Ultra-Low Power Design

**Power Budget Analysis**:
```
Activity                Current    Duration      Energy
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Deep Sleep             0.5μA      29m 50s       0.015mAh
Wake & Sensor Read     50mA       5s            0.069mAh
LoRa Transmission      120mA      3s            0.100mAh
Processing             10mA       2s            0.006mAh
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Total per 30min cycle:                          0.190mAh
Daily consumption (48 cycles):                  9.12mAh
Monthly consumption:                            274mAh
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
With 20Ah battery: 73 months theoretical (2.5 months realistic with 80% DOD, 50% efficiency)
```

**Adaptive Sampling Strategy** (Energy Saving):
```cpp
// Adjust sampling based on rate of change and battery level
uint16_t calculateSleepInterval() {
  float battery_pct = getBatteryPercentage();
  float level_change_rate = abs(current_level - last_level) / time_delta;

  // Emergency power saving
  if(battery_pct < 20) {
    return 7200;  // 2 hours
  }

  // Rapid change detection (potential flooding/drought)
  if(level_change_rate > RAPID_CHANGE_THRESHOLD) {
    return 600;   // 10 minutes
  }

  // Normal operation
  if(battery_pct > 70) {
    return 1800;  // 30 minutes
  } else {
    return 3600;  // 1 hour (power conservation)
  }
}
```

### Enhanced Power System

**Cost-Optimized Solar Configuration**:
```
20W Polycrystalline Panel ($15-25)
     ↓
CN3791 MPPT Charge Controller ($3-5)
     ↓
18650 LiFePO4 Pack (8S1P = 25.6V 3Ah, ~$20)
     ↓
Buck Converter to 3.3V ($1-2)
     ↓
Microcontroller + Sensors
```

**Total Power System Cost**: ~$40-55 (vs $100+ for commercial solutions)

