## 2. ENERGY-OPTIMIZED EDGE DEVICE

### Hardware Selection (Cost vs. Power Trade-offs)

**Option A: STM32L0 Series (Ultra-Low Power)**
- **Model**: STM32L071 (~$2-3 in volume, but availability varies)
- **Advantages**:
  - Deep sleep: ~0.3μA (theoretical minimum; real-world: 1-5μA with peripherals)
  - Industrial temperature range: -40°C to 85°C
  - Better ADC linearity than many alternatives

- **Trade-offs**:
  - Requires external radio module (LoRa/cellular), adding $10-30 to cost
  - Steeper learning curve than Arduino ecosystem
  - May be harder to source in some rural regions
  - Requires ST-Link programmer (~$10-20)

**Option B: Arduino Pro Mini Clone (Maintainability Focus)**
- **Cost**: ~$2-3
- **Advantages**:
  - Widely available globally
  - Extensive community support and examples
  - Local technicians more likely familiar with Arduino
  - Simple USB programming

- **Trade-offs**:
  - Higher sleep current (~5-50μA depending on board modifications)
  - Less efficient power management
  - May require hardware modifications (removing power LED, voltage regulator)
  - 3.3V/

